<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caDonald%20F.%20Hunter%20%281911-1976%29%2C%20was%20born%20on%20January%2022%2C%201911%20to%20Horace%20T.%20Hunter%20and%20Christine%20Fleming%20in%20Toronto%2C%20Ontario.%20He%20was%20educated%20at%20Upper%20Canada%20College%20and%20the%20University%20of%20Toronto%2C%20but%20left%20university%20in%201930%20to%20begin%20working%20in%20the%20audit%20department%20of%20the%20Maclean%20Publishing%20Company.%20In%201938%2C%20he%20was%20appointed%20Managing%20Director%20of%20its%20British%20subsidiary.%20During%20the%20Second%20World%20War%2C%20he%20served%20with%20the%20Governor-General%27s%20Horse%20Guards%2C%20which%20was%20converted%20to%20a%20tank%20regiment.%20He%20went%20overseas%20as%20a%20staff%20captain%20with%20the%205th%20Canadian%20Armored%20Brigade.%20He%20served%20as%20a%20Brigade%20Major%20in%20the%204th%20Canadian%20Armored%20Division%20in%20England%2C%20then%20in%20Italy%20with%20the%20First%20Canadian%20Army%20Tank%20Brigade%2C%20before%20returning%20to%20Canada%20and%20to%20Maclean-Hunter%20as%20manager%20of%20Mayfair%20magazine.%20In%201946%2C%20he%20was%20appointed%20Executive%20Assistant%20to%20T.%20H.%20Howse%2C%20then%20Vice-president%20and%20company%20Treasurer%2C%20and%20he%20became%20involved%20in%20the%20company%27s%20London%20and%20Chicago%20operations.%20He%20was%20also%20closely%20involved%20in%20the%20design%20and%20development%20of%20the%20company%27s%20new%20printing%20plant%2C%20which%20opened%20in%20Willowdale%20in%201948.%20He%20was%20appointed%20Vice-president%20and%20Managing%20Director%20in%201952%2C%20President%20in%201962%2C%20and%20President%20and%20Chairman%20of%20the%20Board%20in%201969.%20He%20was%20President%20of%20the%20Business%20Newspapers%20Association%2C%20and%20a%20Director%20of%20the%20Periodical%20Press%20Association%20of%20Canada%20and%20the%20Audit%20Bureau%20of%20Circulations%20in%20the%20United%20States.%20Hunter%20died%20on%20October%203%2C%201976.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

