<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caHe%20was%20born%20in%20Brockville%2C%20Ontario%20in%201940.%20After%20studying%20political%20science%20and%20journalism%20at%20Ryerson%20Polytechnical%20Institute%20from%201961-1964%2C%20Hoy%20has%20covered%20political%20events%20for%20a%20number%20of%20newspapers%2C%20including%20the%20Toronto%20Telegram%20and%20Toronto%20Star.%20As%20well%2C%20Hoy%20was%20the%20Toronto%20Sun%27s%20Queen%27s%20Park%20columnist%20from%201975-1984.%20He%20has%20since%20become%20the%20Toronto%20Sun%27s%20Ottawa%20political%20correspondent.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caHe%20was%20born%20in%20Stamford%2C%20Connecticut%2C%20and%20married%20Abigail%20Dibble%20in%201760.%20Before%20the%20American%20Revolution%2C%20he%20was%20a%20Justice%20of%20the%20Peace%20for%20the%20City%20and%20County%20of%20Albany.%20In%20the%20fall%20of%201776%2C%20he%20and%20his%20brothers%20formed%20a%20band%20of%20Loyalists%20which%20went%20to%20Canada%20to%20join%20Sir%20Guy%20Carleton%20at%20Crown%20Point.%20In%201777%2C%20he%20was%20made%20a%20Captain%20in%20the%20%22King%27s%20Loyal%20Americans%22%2C%20a%20corps%20of%20Loyalists%20formed%20by%20his%20younger%20brother%2C%20Lt.%20Col.%2C%20Ebenezer%20Jessup.%20In%20November%20of%201781%2C%20this%20corps%20was%20reorganized%2C%20and%20Edward%20Jessup%20was%20appointed%20to%20be%20Major%20Commandant%20to%20a%20corps%20called%20the%20Loyal%20Rangers%20%28sometimes%20referred%20to%20as%20Jessup%27s%20Rangers%29.%20This%20regiment%20was%20disbanded%20in%201783%2C%20and%20in%201784%2C%20Jessup%20worked%20to%20settle%20his%20soldiers%20in%20the%20area%20that%20now%20comprises%20the%20counties%20of%20Leeds%2C%20Grenville%2C%20Addington%2C%20and%20the%20Bay%20of%20Quinte.%20In%201785%2C%20he%20went%20to%20England%20to%20present%20his%20schedule%20of%20losses%20to%20the%20commissioners%20appointed%20for%20inquiry%20into%20the%20losses%20and%20services%20of%20American%20Loyalists.%20In%201787%2C%20he%20proceeded%20to%20Augusta%20Township%2C%20and%20settled%20on%20his%20grant%20of%201200%20acres%20%28he%20was%20also%20granted%203000%20acres%20in%20the%20District%20of%20Lunenburg%29.%20In%201810%2C%20he%20had%20a%20town%20plot%20surveyed%20on%20the%20front%20of%20Lots%202%20and%203%20in%20the%20First%20Concession%20of%20Augusta%20Township%2C%20Grenville%20County%2C%20which%20he%20named%20Prescott%20%28in%20honour%20of%20General%20Robert%20Prescott%2C%20Governor-in-Chief%20of%20Canada%20from%201787-1807%29.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caHe%20was%20born%20in%20Thurlow%20Township%2C%20Hastings%20County%2C%20and%20attended%20Victoria%20College%2C%20Cobourg%2C%20the%20Toronto%20School%20of%20Medicine%20and%20the%20University%20of%20New%20York%2C%20where%20he%20graduated%20in%201854.%20He%20became%20a%20member%20of%20the%20English%20Royal%20College%20of%20Surgeons%20in%201855%20and%20served%20as%20a%20medical%20officer%20in%20the%20Crimean%20War.%20On%20his%20return%20to%20Canada%2C%20he%20practised%20medicine%20at%20Belleville%20and%20Toronto.%20He%20was%20a%20professor%20of%20general%20pathology%20and%20surgery%20at%20Victoria%20College%20and%20Sub-Dean%20of%20the%20Toronto%20Medical%20School.%20He%20was%20also%20the%20first%20Medical%20Health%20Officer%20of%20Toronto%2C%201883-1891.%20Canniff%20was%20also%20the%20author%20of%20two%20historical%20works%20entitled%20A%20History%20of%20the%20early%20settlement%20of%20Upper%20Canada%20%281869%29%2C%20and%20The%20medical%20profession%20in%20Upper%20Canada%3A%20a%20historical%20narrative%20%28Toronto%2C%201894%29.%20Topics%20in%20his%20other%20papers%20included%3A%20the%20Toronto%20General%20Hospital%2C%20the%20Canadian%20Medical%20Association%2C%20Victoria%20College%2C%20settlement%20in%20Belleville%20and%20Prince%20Edward%20County%2C%20the%20Northwest%20Rebellion%20and%20historical%20societies.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

