<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caIn%201968%2C%20the%20Government%20of%20Ontario%2C%20through%20the%20Department%20of%20the%20Attorney%20General%2C%20became%20responsible%20for%20all%20aspects%20of%20the%20administration%20of%20justice%20in%20the%20province.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20the%20Clerks%20of%20the%20Peace%20of%20the%20province%2C%20who%20prior%20to%201968%20were%20local%20county%20officials%2C%20became%20officials%20of%20the%20Department%20of%20the%20Attorney%20General.%20Clerks%20of%20the%20Peace%20were%20appointed%20by%20the%20Lieutenant%20Governor%20and%20were%20required%20to%20be%20a%20Barrister%20at%20Law%2C%20with%20not%20less%20than%20three%20years%20standing%20at%20the%20bar%20of%20Ontario.%20The%20positions%20of%20Clerk%20of%20the%20Peace%20and%20Crown%20Attorney%20were%2C%20in%20general%2C%20held%20by%20the%20same%20individual.%20However%2C%20if%20it%20was%20necessary%20for%20health%20reasons%2C%20the%20individual%20could%20resign%20as%20Crown%20Attorney%20and%20remain%20as%20Clerk%20of%20the%20Peace.%20If%20this%20was%20the%20case%2C%20the%20newly%20appointed%20Crown%20Attorney%20would%20then%20become%20Clerk%20of%20the%20Peace%20upon%20the%20vacancy%20of%20that%20position.%20With%20the%20abolition%20of%20the%20General%20Sessions%20of%20the%20Peace%20in%201984%2C%20the%20position%20of%20Clerk%20of%20the%20Peace%20lost%20much%20of%20its%20remaining%20raison%20d%27etre%20and%20subsequently%20faded%20away%20completely.%20The%20following%20is%20an%20alphabetical%20listing%20of%20the%20counties%2Fdistricts%2Fjudicial%20districts%20that%20have%20existed%20within%20the%20Province%20since%201968%20%28with%20Dt.%3D%20District%2C%20Co.%3DCounty%2C%20and%20J.D.%3DJudicial%20District%29%2C%20along%20with%20the%20dates%20for%20which%20they%20existed%3A%20Algoma%20Dt.%20%281859-%20%29%3B%20%20Brant%20Co.%20%281853-%20%20%20%20%29%3B%20Bruce%20Co.%20%281867-%20%20%20%20%20%29%3B%20Carleton%20Co.%20%281850-1969%29%3B%20Cochrane%20Dt.%20%281922-%20%29%3B%20Dufferin%20Co.%20%281881-%20%20%20%20%20%29%3B%20Durham%20J.D.%20%281974-%20%20%20%20%20%29%3B%20Elgin%20Co.%20%281853-%20%29%3B%20Essex%20Co.%20%281853-%20%20%20%20%20%29%3B%20Frontenac%20Co.%20%281865-%20%20%20%20%20%29%3B%20Grey%20Co.%20%281853-%20%29%3B%20Haldimand%20Co.%20%281851-1974%29%3B%20Haldimand%20J.D.%20%281974-%20%20%20%20%20%29%3B%20Haliburton%20Co.%20%281874-%20%20%20%20%20%29%3B%20Halton%20Co.%20%281855-1973%29%3B%20Halton%20J.D.%20%281974-%20%20%20%20%20%29%3B%20Hamilton-%20Wentworth%20J.D.%20%281974-%20%20%20%20%20%29%3B%20Hastings%20Co.%20%281850-%20%20%20%20%20%29%3B%20Huron%20Co.%20%281867-%20%29%3B%20Kenora%20Dt.%20%281898-%20%20%20%20%20%29%3B%20Kent%20Co.%20%281851-%20%29%3B%20Lambton%20Co.%20%281853-%20%20%20%20%20%29%3B%20Lanark%20and%20Renfrew%20United%20Cos.%20%281850-1866%29%3B%20Lanark%20Co.%20%281866-%20%29%3B%20Leeds%20and%20Grenville%20United%20Cos.%20%281850-%20%20%20%20%20%29%3B%20Lennox%20and%20Addington%20United%20Co.%20%281865-%20%29%3B%20%20Lincoln%2C%20Haldimand%20and%20Welland%20United%20Cos.%20%281850-1851%29%3B%20Lincoln%20and%20Welland%20United%20Cos.%20%281851-1856%29%3B%20Lincoln%20Co.%20%281856-%201970%29%3B%20London%20Dt.%20%281798-1849%29%3B%20Luneburg%20Dt.%20%281788-1792%29%3B%20Manitoulin%20Dt.%20%281899-%20%20%20%20%20%29%3B%20Mecklenburg%20Dt.%20%281788-1792%29%3B%20Middlesex%20Co.%20%281850-1851%3B%201853-%20%29%3B%20Middlesex%20and%20Elgin%20United%20Cos.%20%281851-1853%29%3B%20Midland%20Dt.%20%281792-1849%29%3B%20Montreal%20%281777-%201788%29%3B%20Muskoka%20and%20Parry%20Sound%20Dt.%20%281888-1898%29%3B%20Muskoka%20Dt.%20%281898-%20%29%3B%20Nassau%20Dt.%20%281788-%201792%29%3B%20Newcastle%20Dt.%20%281802-%201849%29%3B%20Niagara%20Dt.%20%281798-1849%29%3B%20Niagara%20North%20J.D.%20%281970-%20%20%20%20%20%29%3B%20Niagara%20South%20J.D.%20%281970-%20%29%3B%20Nipissing%20Dt.%20%281858-%20%20%20%20%20%29%3B%20Norfolk%20Co.%20%281850-1974%29%3B%20Norfolk%20J.D.%20%281974-%20%20%20%20%20%29%3B%20Northumberland%20an