<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caStanding%20committees%20of%20the%20Legislative%20Assembly%20of%20Ontario%20are%20regularly%20established%20within%20ten%20days%20of%20the%20beginning%20of%20each%20Session%20of%20Parliament%2C%20and%20%20report%20to%20the%20Legislature%20on%20matters%20referred%20to%20them.%20They%20do%20not%20have%20the%20authority%20to%20initiate%20investigations%20or%20expand%20their%20mandate.%20This%20committee%2C%20established%20in%201986%2C%20replaced%20the%20Standing%20Committee%20on%20Members%27%20Services%20and%20the%20Standing%20Procedural%20Affairs%20Committee.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

