<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20Advertising%20Branch%20of%20the%20Ontario%20Department%20of%20Tourism%20and%20Information%20prepared%20the%20design%20and%20content%20of%20all%20brochures%20and%20pamphlets%20printed%20and%20distributed%20by%20the%20Department%20and%20for%20handling%20all%20Department%20advertising%20for%20the%20promotion%20of%20tourism.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20Advertising%20Branch%20was%20established%20in%201964%20as%20part%20of%20the%20Information%20and%20Promotion%20Division%20of%20the%20Ontario%20Department%20of%20Tourism%20and%20Information.%20The%20Branch%20ceased%20to%20exist%20in%201972%20%20when%20the%20Department%20of%20Tourism%20and%20Information%20was%20replaced%20by%20the%20Ontario%20Ministry%20of%20Industry%20and%20Tourism.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20Community%20Information%20Services%20unit%20administered%20the%20Community%20Information%20Services%20Program.%20The%20unit%20provided%20functional%20support%20for%20a%20network%20of%20community%20information%20centres%20%28CIC%29%20in%20Ontario%2C%20including%20funding%20through%20grants%2C%20providing%20advice%20on%20information%20management%2C%20staffing%20and%20volunteer%20training%2C%20and%20the%20production%20of%20resource%20material.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20Department%20of%20Lands%20and%20Forests%20was%20established%20in%201920%2C%20when%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Mines%20of%20the%20former%20Department%20of%20Lands%2C%20Forests%20and%20Mines%20was%20elevated%20into%20a%20separate%20department.%20The%20Department%20was%20presided%20over%20by%20the%20Minister%20of%20Lands%20and%20Forests%2C%20who%20was%20assisted%20by%20a%20Deputy%20Minister%20and%20a%20number%20of%20Divisional%20Chiefs.%20Most%20of%20the%20former%20non-mine%20functions%20of%20the%20Department%20of%20Lands%2C%20Forests%20and%20Mines%20were%20continued%20by%20the%20Department%20of%20Lands%20and%20Forests.%20An%20exception%20to%20this%2C%20however%2C%20was%20the%20transfer%20of%20the%20Colonization%20and%20Immigration%20Branch%20to%20the%20Department%20of%20Agriculture%20in%201920.%20In%201926%2C%20the%20Northern%20Development%20Branch%20was%20also%20removed%20from%20the%20Department%20of%20Lands%20and%20Forests%20and%20established%20as%20the%20Department%20of%20Northern%20Development.%20Although%20a%20separate%20Minister%20was%20given%20direction%20over%20this%20Department%2C%20the%20Department%20was%20still%20required%20to%20submit%20its%20annual%20reports%20to%20the%20Minister%20of%20Lands%20and%20Forests%20until%201935.%20In%201941%2C%20the%20Department%20was%20considerably%20reorganized%2C%20and%20many%20of%20the%20branches%20of%20the%20Department%20were%20restructured%20as%20divisions.%20The%20Forestry%20Branch%20was%20divided%20into%20three%20new%20divisions%20-%20the%20Division%20of%20Forest%20Protection%2C%20the%20Division%20of%20Air%20Services%2C%20and%20the%20Division%20of%20Reforestation%3B%20the%20Lands%20Branch%20was%20renamed%20the%20Division%20of%20Land%20and%20Recreational%20Areas%3B%20the%20Surveys%20Branch%20was%20renamed%20the%20Division%20of%20Surveys%3B%20the%20Accounts%20Branch%20was%20renamed%20the%20Division%20of%20Accounts%3B%20and%20the%20Woods%20and%20Forest%20Branch%20was%20renamed%20the%20Division%20of%20Timber%20Management.%20Two%20new%20divisions%20-%20the%20Division%20of%20Law%20and%20the%20Division%20of%20Research%20-%20were%20also%20created%20at%20this%20time.%20Further%20developments%20within%20the%20Department%2C%20between%201941%20and%201972%2C%20included%20the%20transfer%20of%20the%20Games%20and%20Fisheries%20Department%20to%20the%20Department%20of%20Lands%20and%20Forests%2C%20and%20its%20subsequent%20renaming%20as%20the%20Division%20of%20Fish%20and%20Wildlife%2C%20in%201946%3B%20the%20separation%20of%20the%20Division%20of%20Lands%20and%20Recreational%20Parks%20into%20the%20Division%20of%20Lands%20and%20the%20Division%20of%20Parks%2C%20in%201954%3B%20the%20transfer%20of%20the%20Conservation%20Authorities%20Branch%20from%20the%20Department%20of%20Planning%20and%20Development%20in%201962%3B%20and%20the%20renaming%20of%20many%20of%20the%20divisions%20of%20the%20Department%20as%20branches%2C%20in%201959.%20The%20Department%20existed%20until%201972%2C%20when%20it%20amalgamated%20with%20the%20Department%20of%20Mines%20and%20Northern%20Affairs%20to%20form%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Natural%20Resources.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20Department%20of%20Lands%20and%20Forests%20was%20responsible%20for%20developing%2C%20administering%2C%20and%20regulating%20the%20Crown%20Lands%2C%20forests%2C%20fish%20and%20wildlife%20of%20the%20Province.%20Specific%20responsibilities%20of%20the%20Department%20included%20forest%20protection%20and%20forest%20fire%20fighting%2C%20control%20and%20sale%20of%20crown%20lands%2C%20reforestation%20and%20timber%20management%2C%20and%20research%20into%20forest%20management.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20Division%20of%20Reforestation%20was%20created%20in%201941%20within%20the%20Ontario%20Department%20of%20Lands%20and%20Forests.%20It%20was%20created%20when%20the%20former%20Forestry%20Branch%20was%20divided%20into%20the%20Division%20of%20Forest%20Protection%2C%20Division%20of%20Air%20Services%20and%20Division%20of%20Reforestation.%20The%20division%20was%20known%20until%201942%20as%20the%20Division%20of%20Reforestation%20and%20Conservation.%20In%201957%2C%20the%20Division%20of%20Reforestation%20and%20the%20Division%20of%20Timber%20Management%20were%20merged%20to%20form%20the%20Division%20of%20Timber.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20Division%20of%20Reforestation%20was%20responsible%20for%20reforestation%20programs%20in%20Ontario%2C%20including%20the%20operation%20of%20forest%20nurseries%2C%20municipal%20reforestation%2C%20distributing%20trees%20to%20private%20land%20owners%2C%20developing%20county%20forests%2C%20roadside%20tree%20planting%20and%20planting%20for%20the%20purposes%20of%20watershed%20protection.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20Division%20of%20Surveys%20and%20Engineering%20conducted%20ground%20and%20aerial%20surveys%20of%20timber%2C%20land%20and%20water%20resources%2C%20the%20leasing%20of%20water%20power%20on%20Crown%20lands%20and%20the%20approval%20of%20plans%20for%20the%20construction%20of%20dams%20in%20Ontario.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20Division%20of%20Surveys%20of%20the%20Ontario%20Department%20of%20Lands%20and%20Forests%20was%20renamed%20the%20Division%20of%20Surveys%20and%20Engineering%20in%201944%2C%20when%20it%20was%20given%20responsibility%20over%20the%20leasing%20of%20water%20power%20on%20Crown%20lands%20and%20authority%20to%20approve%20plans%20for%20the%20construction%20of%20dams.%20The%20Division%20was%20headed%20by%20C.H.%20Fullerton%20%281944-1947%29%2C%20and%20by%20F.W.%20Beatty%20from%201947-1957.%20The%20Division%20consisted%20of%20two%20sections%20-%20the%20Ground%20Surveys%20Section%20and%20the%20Aerial%20Surveys%20Section.%20On%20December%201%2C%201957%2C%20the%20Division%20of%20Surveys%20and%20Engineering%20and%20the%20Division%20of%20Lands%20were%20amalgamated%20under%20the%20title%20of%20the%20Division%20of%20Surveys%20%28renamed%20the%20Lands%20and%20Surveys%20Branch%20in%201960%29.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20Employment%20Service%20Council%20of%20Ontario%20was%20designed%20to%20made%20recommendations%20to%20the%20Minister%20of%20Labour%20with%20regards%20to%20the%20establishment%20and%20operation%20of%20Ontario%20offices%20of%20the%20Employment%20Service%20of%20Canada.%20The%20council%20divided%20itself%20into%20three%20committees%3A%20one%20for%20general%20administration%20of%20the%20Employment%20Service%3B%20one%20for%20Private%20Employment%20Agencies%3B%20and%20one%20for%20other%20questions%20of%20public%20policy>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20Employment%20Service%20Council%20of%20Ontario%20was%20established%20on%20August%203%2C%201922.%20It%20is%20not%20known%20how%20long%20the%20council%20continued%20in%20operation%20but%20it%20appears%20in%20the%20annual%20reports%20up%20until%20about%201940.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20Energy%20Division%20provided%20a%20structure%20for%20identifying%20strategic%20issues%2C%20coordinating%20policy%20and%20program%20development%20and%20integrating%20interaction%20between%20the%20ministry%20and%20other%20governments%20on%20issues%20related%20to%20affordable%20energy%2C%20energy%20regulation%20and%20economic%20growth%2C%20among%20others.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20Energy%20Division%20was%20formed%20in%201997%20as%20part%20of%20the%20newly%20created%20Ministry%20of%20Energy%2C%20Science%20and%20Technology%20out%20of%20portions%20of%20the%20Policy%20Division%20of%20the%20former%20Ministry%20of%20Environment%20and%20Energy.%20At%20various%20times%20during%20its%20history%2C%20the%20Energy%20Division%20included%20the%20Electricity%20Policy%20Branch%3B%20the%20Electricity%20Restructuring%20Office%3B%20the%20Energy%20Policy%20Branch%3B%20the%20Energy%20Economics%20and%20Financial%20Analysis%20Section%20and%20the%20Oil%20and%20Gas%20Section%2C%20among%20others.%20The%20Energy%20Division%20was%20placed%20back%20under%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Environment%20and%20Energy%20when%20that%20Ministry%20was%20briefly%20re-established%20from%20April%202002-August%202002.%20The%20Energy%20Division%20continued%20to%20exist%20as%20part%20of%20the%20newly%20created%20Ministry%20of%20Energy%20in%202003%20but%2C%20in%202004%2C%20its%20responsibilities%20were%20transferred%20to%20the%20Office%20of%20Energy%20Supply%20and%20Conservation.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20Forest%20Protection%20Branch%20was%20created%20within%20the%20Ontario%20Department%20of%20Lands%20and%20Forests%20in%201960%2C%20replacing%20the%20Division%20of%20Forest%20Protection.%20The%20branch%20was%20comprised%20of%20the%20Forest%20Protection%20Section%20and%20for%20Air%20Services%20Section.%20In%201969%2C%20the%20Engineering%20Services%20Section%20was%20also%20formed%20as%20part%20of%20the%20branch.%20The%20Forest%20Protection%20Branch%20ceased%20to%20exist%20in%201971.%20The%20Forest%20Protection%20Section%20and%20Air%20Services%20Section%20became%20part%20of%20the%20Environmental%20Protection%20Branch%2C%20and%20the%20Engineering%20Services%20Section%20became%20part%20of%20the%20Surveys%20and%20Engineering%20Branch.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20Forest%20Protection%20Branch%20was%20responsible%20for%20protecting%20Ontario%27s%20forests%20from%20fire%2C%20insects%20and%20disease.%20It%20also%20operated%20and%20maintained%20an%20aircraft%20fleet%20to%20meet%20the%20flying%20requirements%20of%20the%20Department%20of%20Lands%20and%20Forests%20and%20other%20Departments%20of%20the%20Government%20of%20Ontario.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20Hamilton%20Normal%20School%20was%20an%20educational%20institution%20which%20trained%20teachers%2C%20primarily%20for%20the%20primary%20level%20of%20schools.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20Hamilton%20Normal%20School%20was%20established%20in%201908.%20In%201953%2C%20the%20Hamilton%20Normal%20School%20became%20known%20as%20the%20Hamilton%20Teachers%27%20College%20%28all%20Normal%20Schools%20were%20re-named%20Teachers%27%20Colleges%20at%20this%20time%29.%20In%201974%2C%20the%20Hamilton%20Teachers%27%20College%20was%20reorganized%20as%20the%20Hamilton%20campus%20of%20the%20newly%20created%20Ontario%20Teacher%20Education%20College%3B%20there%20was%20also%20a%20Toronto%20campus.%20In%201979%2C%20the%20Ontario%20Teacher%20Education%20College%2C%20including%20the%20Hamilton%20campus%2C%20was%20closed.%20The%20Hamilton%20building%2C%20beside%20McMaster%20University%2C%20was%20sold%20to%20the%20Hamilton-Wentworth%20Roman%20Catholic%20Separate%20School%20Board%20for%20use%20as%20a%20high%20school.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20Inquiry%20into%20Motor%20Vehicle%20Accident%20Compensation%20in%20Ontario%20conducted%20research%20into%20the%20provision%20of%20insurance%20for%20motor%20vehicle%20accidents%2C%20particularly%20the%20provision%20of%20%22no-fault%22%20insurance.%20The%20Inquiry%20also%20examined%20the%20benefits%20of%20a%20publicly%20owned%20insurance%20system.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20Inquiry%20into%20Motor%20Vehicle%20Accident%20Compensation%20in%20Ontario%20was%20appointed%20on%20November%206%2C%201986.%20The%20Inquiry%20was%20headed%20by%20a%20Commissioner%2C%20the%20Hon.%20Mr.%20Justice%20Coulter%20A.A.%20Osborne%2C%20who%20was%20assisted%20by%20an%20Advisory%20Committee%20of%20ten%20members.%20The%20Committee%20was%20composed%20of%20experts%20in%20the%20field%20of%20automobile%20accident%20compensation%2C%20including%20representatives%20from%20insurance%20bureaus%20and%20companies%2C%20consumer%27s%20assocations%2C%20the%20handicapped%20and%20other%20groups.%20The%20Inquiry%20conducted%20in-depth%20research%20into%20all%20facets%20of%20automobile%20insurance%20in%20Ontario%2C%20including%20standard%20automobile%20insurance%20contracts%2C%20the%20history%20of%20insurance%2C%20litigated%20claims%2C%20and%20a%20wide%20variety%20of%20methods%20of%20providing%20adequate%20insurance%20to%20drivers%20in%20Ontario%20and%20elsewhere.%20The%20Inquiry%20concluded%20that%20no-fault%20benefits%20should%20be%20substantially%20expanded%20and%20made%20truly%20%22no-fault%22%20in%20their%20character%2C%20and%20that%20the%20right%20to%20individual%20compensation%20in%20the%20tort%20system%20should%20be%20maintained.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20the%20need%20to%20sue%20to%20receive%20compensation%20was%20reduced%20although%20the%20right%20to%20sue%20was%20preserved.%20The%20Inquiry%20did%20not%20recommend%20public%20ownership%20of%20the%20insurance%20industry%20in%20Ontario%2C%20but%20rather%20closer%20regulation%20of%20the%20industry.%20The%20inquiry%20made%20a%20great%20number%20of%20detailed%20recommendations%20about%20regulation%20of%20the%20automobile%20insurance%20industry%2C%20insurance%20coverage%20and%20premiums%2C%20systems%20of%20compensation%2C%20other%20insurance%20issues%2C%20public%20or%20private%20provision%20of%20insurance%2C%20rate%20regulation%2C%20and%20accident%20prevention.%20The%20inquiry%20was%20dissolved%20in%201988.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20Land%20Management%20Division%20was%20created%20in%201971%20within%20the%20Department%20of%20Lands%20and%20Forests.%20It%20oversaw%20the%20activities%20of%20the%20Environmental%20Protection%20Branch%2C%20the%20Lands%20and%20Waters%20Branch%2C%20and%20the%20Surveys%20and%20the%20Engineering%20Branch.%20The%20division%20was%20eliminated%20at%20the%20time%20of%20the%20creation%20of%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Natural%20Resources%20on%20April%201%2C%201972.%20Within%20the%20new%20ministry%2C%20its%20functions%20were%20assumed%20by%20the%20Division%20of%20Lands%20and%20the%20Field%20Services%20Division.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20Land%20Management%20Division%20was%20responsible%20for%20forest%20protection%2C%20environmental%20quality%2C%20air%20services%2C%20lands%20and%20waters%20resources%20and%20surveys%20and%20engineering%20in%20Ontario.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20Management%20Information%20Systems%20Branch%20of%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Community%20and%20Social%20Services%20was%20established%20in%201972.%20It%20had%20several%20minor%20name%20changes%20over%20the%20years.%20It%20formed%20part%20of%20the%20Finance%20and%20Administration%20Division.%20In%201986%2C%20the%20Management%20Information%20Systems%20Branch%20disappeared%2C%20and%20its%20functions%20%20were%20assumed%20by%20the%20newly%20established%20Information%20Systems%20and%20Applied%20Technology%20Division.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20Management%20Information%20Systems%20Branch%20planned%20and%20controlled%20the%20development%20and%20operation%20of%20information%20and%20information%20technology%20systems%20for%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Community%20and%20Social%20Services.%20In%20later%20years%2C%20the%20Branch%20dealt%20almost%20exclusively%20with%20the%20management%20of%20computerized%20information.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20Milton%20Jail%20was%20a%20%20maximum%20security%20correctional%20facility%20providing%20short%20term%2C%20secure%20custody%20for%20persons%20awaiting%20trial%20or%20sentencing%2C%20those%20being%20held%20for%20immigration%20hearings%20or%20deportation%2C%20those%20serving%20short%20sentences%20%28under%2090%20days%29%20and%20those%20awaiting%20transfer%20to%20other%20Ontario%20correctional%20institutions%20or%20to%20federal%20institutions.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20Milton%20Jail%20was%20opened%20in%201863%20and%20closed%20in%201978.%20Until%201968%2C%20all%20jails%20in%20Ontario%20were%20administered%20locally%20through%20municipal%20bodies%20under%20the%20guidance%20of%20the%20Ontario%20provincial%20government.%20Responsibility%20for%20jails%20within%20the%20government%20fell%20to%20the%20Office%20of%20the%20Inspector%20of%20Prisons%20and%20Public%20Charities%20%281868-1934%29%2C%20the%20Reformatories%20and%20Prisons%20Branch%20of%20the%20Department%20of%20the%20Provincial%20Secretary%20%281934-1946%29%2C%20and%20the%20Department%20of%20Reform%20Institutions%20%281946-1968%29.%20In%201968%2C%20their%20administration%20was%20assumed%20directly%20by%20the%20provincial%20government.%20Since%20then%2C%20jails%20have%20been%20administered%20within%20the%20Department%20of%20Correctional%20Services%20%281968-1972%29%2C%20and%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Correctional%20Services%20%281972-1993%29.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20Ministry%20of%20Enterprise%2C%20Opportunity%20and%20Innovation%20was%20created%20in%202002.%20It%20was%20superceded%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Economic%20Development%20and%20Trade%20in%20October%2C%202003.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20Ministry%20of%20Enterprise%2C%20Opportunity%20and%20Innovation%20was%20responsible%20for%20promoting%20innovation%2C%20economic%20growth%2C%20support%20services%2C%20investment%20and%20exports%20and%20job%20creation%20in%20Ontario%2C%20by%20providing%20leadership%20in%20the%20development%20of%20economic%20and%20science%20and%20technology%20policy%20across%20the%20government.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20North%20Bay%20Psychiatric%20Hospital%20%28NBPH%29%20was%20established%20in%20October%201957%20by%20the%20Mental%20Health%20Division%20of%20the%20Department%20of%20Health.%20Encompassing%20Northeastern%20Ontario%2C%20NBPH%27s%20catchment%20area%20covered%20close%20to%20one%20third%20of%20the%20province%20of%20Ontario.%20Inpatient%20services%20were%20provided%20through%20four%20functional%20programs%3A%20District%20Mental%20Health%20Program%2C%20Regional%20Specialized%20Mental%20Health%20Program%2C%20Seniors%27%20Mental%20Health%20Program%20and%20the%20Forensic%20Program.%20In%20addition%20to%20its%20acute%20care%20role%2C%20the%20hospital%20served%20as%20the%20region%27s%20tertiary%20care%20centre%20with%20a%20large%20proportion%20of%20beds%20dedicated%20to%20long%20term%20rehabilitation%20and%20care%20of%20those%20with%20serious%20mental%20illness.%20Care%20and%20treatment%20of%20the%20mentally%20disordered%20offender%20population%20and%20patients%20referred%20by%20the%20courts%20was%20an%20important%20service%20of%20the%20hospital.%20Small%20rural%20and%20isolated%20areas%20depended%20heavily%20on%20NBPH%20for%20the%20provision%20of%20acute%20care%20services.%20The%20Northeastern%20Regional%20Mental%20Health%20Centre%20was%20closed%20March%2031%2C%201975%3A%20patients%20were%20transferred%20to%20the%20North%20Bay%20Psychiatric%20Hospital.%20The%20Hospital%20was%20divested%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Health%20and%20Long-Term%20Care%20on%2021%20November%202005.%20It%20was%20known%20as%20the%20North%20Bay%20site%20of%20the%20Northeast%20Mental%20Health%20Centre%20until%201%20April%202011%20when%20the%20Northeast%20Mental%20Health%20Centre%20amalgamated%20with%20the%20North%20Bay%20General%20Hospital.%20It%20is%20now%20known%20as%20the%20North%20Bay%20Regional%20Health%20Centre%20%28NBRHC%29.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20North%20Bay%20Psychiatric%20Hospital%20functioned%20as%20an%20accredited%20mental%20health%20facility%20providing%20inpatient%20programs%2C%20community%20programs%20and%20services%2C%20and%20consultation%20and%20education%20programs.%20North%20Bay%20also%20provided%20curriculum%20training%20in%20Chronic%20Care%20psychiatry%20sponsored%20by%20the%20University%20of%20Western%20Ontario.%20The%20hospital%20was%20also%20used%20by%20many%20nursing%20programs%20in%20the%20region%20for%20their%20psychiatric%20training.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20Northern%20Telephone%20Company%20was%20founded%20in%20New%20Liskeard%2C%20Temiskaming%20District%2C%20Ontario%20on%20April%205%2C%201905.%20It%20was%20originally%20called%20the%20Temiskaming%20Telephone%20Company.%20Its%20range%20of%20customers%20expanded%20regularly%20over%20the%20next%2050%20years%2C%20through%20purchases%20of%20other%20telephone%20companies.%20The%20first%20of%20these%20was%20the%20Kirkland%20Lake%20and%20Swastika%20Telephone%20System%2C%20bought%20in%201921.%20In%201928%20the%20company%20changed%20its%20name%20to%20Northern%20Telephone%20Company%20Limited.%20In%201966%2C%20Bell%20Canada%20acquired%20a%20controlling%20share%20in%20the%20company%20through%20stock%20purchases%2C%20although%20it%20continued%20to%20exist%20as%20a%20separate%20entity.%20In%201985%20the%20company%20was%20still%20operational.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20Office%20of%20the%20Provincial%20Municipal%20Auditor%20was%20established%20in%201897.%20The%20Auditor%20reported%20to%20the%20Attorney%20General%20of%20Ontario%20from%201897%20to%201914%2C%20and%20after%20that%20to%20the%20Provincial%20Secretary.%20The%20Provincial%20Municipal%20Auditor%20was%20transferred%20to%20the%20newly%20created%20Bureau%20of%20Municipal%20Affairs%20in%201917.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20Ontario%20Committee%20on%20Student%20Awards%20was%20first%20appointed%20by%20the%20Minister%20of%20University%20Affairs%20in%201966%20as%20an%20ad%20hoc%20advisory%20board%20on%20policies%20relating%20to%20financial%20assistance%20to%20students%20in%20all%20areas%20of%20post-secondary%20education.%20The%20committee%20was%20broadly%20representative%20of%20the%20academic%20community%20in%20Ontario%2C%20including%20administrators%2C%20faculty%20and%20students%20from%20both%20the%20universities%20and%20colleges%20of%20applied%20arts%20and%20technology%20as%20well%20as%20members%20of%20the%20Department%20and%20of%20the%20Association%20of%20Student%20Awards%20Officers.%20The%20Committee%20appears%20to%20have%20been%20alternatively%20known%20as%20The%20Ontario%20Student%20Awards%20Committee%20%28OSAC%29.%20It%20continued%20to%20exist%20after%20the%20formation%20of%20the%20Department%20%28later%20Ministry%29%20of%20Colleges%20and%20Universities%20in%201971.%20After%20an%20internal%20review%20by%20the%20Management%20Committee%20of%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Colleges%20and%20Universities%20in%201974%2C%20the%20Committee%20on%20Student%20Awards%20was%20replaced%20by%20a%20joint%20subcommittee%20of%20the%20Ontario%20Comittee%20on%20University%20Affairs%20and%20the%20Council%20of%20Regents.%20The%20Committee%20on%20Student%20Awards%20voted%20itself%20out%20of%20existence%20in%20February%201974%20and%20dissolved%20on%20March%2031%2C%201974.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20Ontario%20Telephone%20Service%20Commission%20was%20formed%20on%20April%201%2C%201960%20replacing%20the%20former%20Ontario%20Telephone%20Authority.%20It%20was%20located%20within%20the%20Department%20of%20Agriculture%20and%20Food.%20On%2023%20June%201971%20it%20became%20part%20of%20the%20Department%2C%20later%20the%20Ministry%2C%20of%20Transportation%20and%20Communications.%20In%201987%2C%20it%20was%20moved%20to%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Culture%20and%20Communications%2C%20and%20finally%20became%20part%20of%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Economic%20Development%20and%20Trade%20in%201993%20when%20that%20ministry%20became%20responsible%20for%20communications%20policy%20and%20programs.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20Canada%20ruled%20in%20Spring%201994%20that%20communications%20was%20the%20responsibility%20of%20the%20CRTC%20%28the%20federal%20communications%20regulatory%20body%29.%20The%20Ontario%20Telephone%20Services%20Commission%20was%20consequently%20closed%20down%20in%20the%20Fall%20of%201994.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20Ontario%20Telephone%20Services%20Commission%20was%20a%20provincial%2C%20quasi-%20judicial%20regulatory%20body%20responsible%20for%20hearing%20and%20deciding%20all%20applications%20filed%20by%20the%20industry%20as%20well%20as%20by%20the%20public.%20The%20Commission%20issued%20orders%20and%20directions%20for%20the%20regulation%20of%20the%20thirty%20independent%20telephone%20systems%20in%20Ontario%2C%20and%20ensured%20that%20rates%20charged%20for%20services%20were%20just%20and%20reasonable%20and%20that%20efficient%20and%20adequate%20services%20were%20provided%20to%20the%20systems%20customers.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20Operations%20Branch%20administered%20the%20construction%20and%20maintenance%20of%20King%27s%20Highways%20and%20secondary%20roads%20in%20Ontario.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20Operations%20Branch%20was%20established%20in%201954%20within%20the%20Ontario%20Department%20of%20Highways.%20The%20Operations%20Branch%20was%20comprised%20of%20three%20sections%20%28later%20called%20divisions%29%3A%20Construction%3B%20%20Maintenance%3B%20and%20Materials%20and%20Research%20%28in%201964%2C%20Material%20and%20Research%20was%20divided%20into%20two%20offices%2C%20one%20of%20which%20-%20the%20Materials%20Testing%20Office%20-%20remained%20within%20the%20Operations%20Branch%29.%20In%201962%20the%20Municipal%20Roads%20Division%20was%20added%20to%20the%20branch.%20In%201971%2C%20the%20Operations%20Branch%20became%20part%20of%20the%20Ontario%20Department%20of%20Transportation%20and%20Communications.%20In%201972%2C%20the%20Operations%20Branch%20was%20replaced%20by%20the%20Operations%20Division%2C%20within%20the%20Ontario%20Ministry%20of%20Transportation%20and%20Communications.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20Principe%20Umberto%20Lodge%20of%20the%20Order%20Sons%20of%20Italy%20of%20Canada%20was%20established%20in%201917%20in%20St.%20Catharines.%20In%201938%2C%20after%20the%20Order%20underwent%20a%20significant%20period%20of%20growth%2C%20Principe%20Umberto%20divided%20to%20allow%20for%20the%20formation%20of%20a%20separate%20lodge%20for%20its%20female%20members.%20This%20lodge%2C%20called%20Savoia%2C%20lasted%20under%20ten%20years%2C%20after%20which%20time%20it%20was%20re-incorporated%20into%20the%20main%20lodge.%20The%20Principe%20Umberto%20Lodge%20was%20unable%20to%20re-build%20its%20membership%20after%20WWII%20and%20it%20consequently%20dissolved%20in%20the%20early%201971.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20Provincial%20Municipal%20Auditor%20was%20responsible%20for%20devising%20accounting%20procedures%20for%20the%20various%20levels%20of%20local%20government%20across%20Ontario%2C%20for%20auditing%20the%20books%20of%20these%20municipalities%2C%20and%20for%20preparing%20books%20of%20account%20for%20use%20by%20the%20various%20school%20boards%20of%20the%20province.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20Research%20Branch%20of%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Education%20was%20created%20in%201981%20and%20resulted%20from%20a%20combination%20of%20the%20Research%20and%20Evaluation%20Branch%20and%20the%20Information%20Centre%20%28previously%20named%20the%20Information%20Resources%20Centre%29.%20The%20Research%20Branch%20was%20part%20of%20the%20Planning%20and%20Policy%20Analysis%20Division.%20The%20Research%20Branch%20ceased%20to%20exist%20when%20it%20was%20merged%20with%20the%20Statistical%20Information%20Services%20Unit%20of%20the%20former%20Management%20Information%20Systems%20Branch%20to%20form%20the%20Research%20and%20Information%20Branch%2C%20effective%20January%201%2C%201984.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20Research%20Branch%20was%20responsible%20for%20the%20Ontario%20Ministry%20of%20Education%27s%20educational%20research%20program.%20The%20Research%20Branch%20developed%20systems%20that%20would%20evaluate%20Ministry%20of%20Education%20programs%20and%20the%20provincial%20education%20system.%20The%20Research%20Branch%20was%20also%20responsible%20for%20the%20Information%20Centre%20of%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Education%20and%20for%20the%20Ontario%20Education%20Resources%20Information%20Systems%20%28ONTERIS%29%2C%20which%20developed%20data%20bases%20providing%20information%20on%20education%20research%20and%20documents.%20The%20Research%20Branch%20provided%20similar%20services%20to%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Colleges%20and%20Universities.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20Select%20Committee%20on%20Common%20and%20Grammar%20Schools%20was%20appointed%20to%20examine%20allegations%20that%20Upper%20Canada%20College%20was%20absorbing%20a%20disproportionate%20share%20of%20the%20original%20endowment%20for%20the%20support%20of%20university%20education%20in%20the%20province%20and%20to%20examine%20its%20role%20within%20the%20general%20system%20of%20education%20in%20the%20province.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20Standing%20Committee%20on%20the%20Legislative%20Assembly%20examines%20all%20rules%2C%20regulations%20and%20conventions%20relating%20to%20the%20operation%20of%20the%20Legislative%20Assembly%20of%20Ontario%2C%20including%20matters%20of%20members%20privileges%2C%20the%20role%20of%20the%20Speaker%20and%20the%20rules%20of%20debate.%20It%20also%20examines%20services%20available%20to%20members%20of%20the%20Legislative%20Assembly%2C%20including%20the%20operations%20of%20the%20Legislative%20Library%2C%20food%20services%2C%20printing%2C%20secretarial%20staffing%20and%20other%20issues.%20It%20acts%20as%20an%20advisor%20on%20the%20broadcasting%20of%20the%20sessions%20of%20the%20house.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20Trade%20Development%20Branch%20was%20formed%20in%201993%20in%20the%20Ontario%20Ministry%20of%20Economic%20Development%20and%20Trade%20within%20the%20Trade%20and%20Investment%20Marketing%20Division.%20It%20assumed%20some%20of%20the%20responsibilities%20of%20the%20former%20Trade%20and%20Investment%20Support%20Branch.%20The%20branch%20consisted%20at%20creation%20of%20the%20Export%20Services%20Section%2C%20the%20Americas%20Section%20and%20the%20Overseas%20Section.%20These%20last%20two%20sections%20assumed%20some%20of%20the%20responsibilities%20of%20the%20former%20international%20offices%20of%20the%20ministry%2C%20which%20were%20closed%20in%201993.%20In%201996%20the%20Trade%20Development%20Branch%20ceased%20to%20exist%20when%20its%20functions%20were%20assumed%20by%20the%20Ontario%20International%20Trade%20Corporation.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20Trade%20Development%20Branch%20was%20responsible%20for%20promoting%20Ontario%20exports%20internationally.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20Trade%20Division%20was%20formed%20when%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Industry%20and%20Tourism%20was%20replaced%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Industry%20and%20Trade%20in%201982.%20It%20had%20no%20immediate%20predecessor%2C%20but%20acquired%20some%20functions%20from%20the%20Industry%20Division%20%28which%20continued%20to%20exist%20after%201982%29%20and%20from%20the%20Policy%20and%20Priorities%20Division.%20Within%20the%20new%20division%2C%20two%20branches%20were%20created%3A%20the%20International%20Trade%20and%20Investment%20Branch%2C%20and%20the%20Trade%20Policy%20and%20Analysis%20Branch.%20The%20division%20was%20also%20responsible%20for%20administering%20the%20international%20offices%20of%20the%20ministry.%20The%20Trade%20Division%20ceased%20to%20exist%20when%20parts%20of%20the%20Trade%20Division%20and%20the%20Industry%20Division%20were%20combined%20together%20in%20a%20single%2C%20new%20division%20in%20November%2C%201986%2C%20known%20as%20Industry%20and%20Trade%20Expansion.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20Trade%20Division%20was%20responsible%20for%20the%20promotion%20of%20exports%20of%20Ontario%20products%20internationally.%20This%20was%20accomplished%20through%20export%20seminars%2C%20trade%20missions%20and%20fairs%2C%20market%20research%2C%20and%20policy%20advocacy.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20Transportation%20Regulation%20Operations%20Division%20regulated%20the%20licensing%20of%20vehicles%20covered%20by%20the%20Public%20Vehicles%20Act%20%28e.g.%20buses%20and%20charter%20bus%20operations%2C%20for-hire%20trucks%29.%20The%20division%20also%20monitored%20the%20performance%20and%20qualifications%20of%20Ontario%20drivers%20and%20vehicles%20and%20provided%20information%20on%20this%20to%20the%20public%2C%20courts%2C%20and%20law%20enforcement%20agencies.%20In%20addition%2C%20this%20agency%20investigated%20possible%20contraventions%20to%20various%20transportation%20acts%20and%20monitored%20the%20operation%20of%20carriers.%20After%201980%2C%20the%20division%20offered%20systems%20support%20for%20all%20agencies%20administered%20by%20the%20Safety%20and%20Regulation%20Division.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20Transportation%20Regulation%20Operations%20Division%20was%20formed%20in%20January%201976%20within%20the%20Ontario%20Ministry%20of%20Transportation%20and%20Communications%2C%20assuming%20the%20administrative%20functions%20of%20the%20Licensing%20Control%20Division%20as%20well%20as%20responsibility%20for%20the%20newly%20created%20Program%20Development%20Branch.%20The%20Transportation%20Regulation%20Operations%20Division%20was%20initially%20known%20as%20the%20Transportation%20and%20Regulation%20Division%20and%20reported%20to%20the%20Assistant%20Deputy%20Minister%20of%20Drivers%20and%20Vehicles%20between%201976%20and%201979%20%28changing%20its%20name%20to%20the%20Transportation%20Regulation%20Division%20in%201977%29.%20From%201980%20until%20its%20closure%2C%20the%20Assistant%20Deputy%20Minister%20of%20Safety%20and%20Regulation%20administered%20the%20division.%20The%20agency%20changed%20its%20name%20to%20the%20Transportation%20Regulation%20Operations%20Division%20in%201981.%20The%20division%20ceased%20to%20exist%20in%201991%20when%20the%20subordinate%20branches%20that%20it%20administered%20began%20reporting%20directly%20to%20the%20Assistant%20Deputy%20Minister%20of%20the%20Safety%20and%20Regulation%20Division.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20Travel%20Services%20Branch%20promoted%20Ontario%20tourism%20and%20facilities%2C%20both%20domestically%20and%20internationally%2C%20through%20mass%20advertising%20and%20promotion%20in%20the%20media%2C%20preparation%20of%20tourism%20publications%2C%20programs%20to%20expand%20sales%20of%20Ontario%20tours%20and%20facilities%20by%20travel%20agents%20and%20operators%2C%20travel%20counselling%2C%20special%20promotions%2C%20and%20the%20distribution%20of%20travel%20films%20produced%20by%20the%20ministry.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20War%20Memorial%20Committee%20of%20Ontario%20was%20established%20following%20%20a%20resolution%20of%20the%20Legislative%20Assembly%20calling%20for%20a%20suitable%20mark%20of%20appreciation%20for%20those%20who%20had%20been%20killed%20during%20the%20First%20World%20War.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20function%20of%20this%20branch%20is%20to%20coordinate%20the%20programs%20and%20services%20that%20administer%20the%20Occupational%20Health%20and%20Safety%20Act%20and%20its%20regulations.%20It%20aims%20to%20foster%20a%20healthy%20and%20safe%20working%20environment%20and%20to%20encourage%20cooperation%20between%20employers%20and%20workers%20in%20identifying%20and%20controlling%20health%20and%20safety%20hazards.%20The%20branch%20operates%20the%20following%20programs%3A%20Professional%20and%20Specialized%20Services%2C%20Industrial%20Health%20and%20Safety%20Program%2C%20Construction%20Health%20and%20Safety%20Program%2C%20Mining%20Health%20and%20Safety%20Program%2C%20Mine%20Rescue%20Program%2C%20Regulation%20Development%20Unit%2C%20Health%20and%20Safety%20Studies%20Unit%20%28amalgamated%20with%20Professional%20and%20Specialized%20Services%20in%201996-97%29%2C%20Occupational%20Health%20Laboratory%20Services%2C%20Materials%20Testing%20Laboratory%2C%20Radiation%20Protection%20Services.%20The%20services%20are%20provided%20in%20the%20Area%2C%20District%20and%20Satellite%20Offices%20across%20the%20province.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20future%20Ontario%20Concentrated%20Milk%20Producers%27%20Marketing%20Board%20began%20when%20concentrated%20milk%20producers%20were%20represented%20on%20the%20Board%20of%20the%20Ontario%20Milk%20and%20Cream%20Producers%27%20Association%20from%201917%20to%201932.%20From%201933%20to%201934%2C%20these%20producers%20were%20supported%20by%20the%20Ontario%20Whole%20Milk%20Producers%27%20Association.%20In%201934%2C%20the%20Ontario%20Manufactured%20Milk%20Producers%27%20Association%20was%20created%20to%20establish%20minimum%20milk%20prices.%20In%201937%2C%20their%20name%20was%20changed%20to%20the%20Ontario%20Concentrated%20Producers%27%20Association.%20The%20Association%20became%20incorporated%20under%20the%20Agricultural%20Associations%20Act%20in%201944.%20As%20a%20result%20of%20the%20Farm%20Products%20Marketing%20Act%2C%20the%20Association%27s%20name%20changed%20in%201954%20to%20the%20Ontario%20Concentrated%20Milk%20Producers%27%20Marketing%20Board.%20The%20Ontario%20Concentrated%20Milk%20Producers%27%20Marketing%20Board%20surrendered%20its%20charter%20in%201966%20with%20its%20assets%20and%20liabilities%20being%20transferred%20to%20the%20Ontario%20Milk%20Marketing%20Board.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20primary%20mandate%20of%20the%20Ontario%20Committee%20on%20Student%20Awards%20was%20%22to%20ensure%20a%20clear%20articulation%20of%20the%20financial%20arrangements%20that%20will%20be%20required%20to%20ensure%20that%20all%20students%20have%20the%20necessary%20resources%20to%20undertake%20post-secondary%20education.%22%20%20A%20full%20statement%20of%20the%20%22Terms%20of%20Reference%22%20can%20be%20found%20in%20Appendix%20B-1%20of%20the%20Annual%20Report%2C%20University%20Affairs%2C%201969-70%2C%20p.%2021.%20In%20addition%20to%20the%20detailed%20study%20of%20current%20programs%20of%20student%20financial%20assistance%2C%20the%20Committee%20initiated%20several%20research%20projects%2C%20resulting%20in%20the%20preparation%20of%20the%20Cook-Stager%20Report%20%28A%20Study%20of%20Programs%20for%20Financial%20Assistance%20to%20Students%20in%20the%20Province%20of%20Ontario%29%2C%20part%20of%20which%20was%20developed%20as%20the%20Clarke-Kent%20Report%20%28Student%20Aid%20and%20Access%20to%20Higher%20Education%20in%20Ontario%29.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThis%20Act%20permitted%20communities%20to%20petition%20the%20Legislative%20Assembly%20or%20county%20for%20incorporation%20as%20townships%2C%20towns%20or%20villages%20on%20reaching%20specified%20population%20levels.%20An%20incorporated%20township%2C%20lower%20tier%20municipality%2C%20has%20a%20council%20consisting%20of%20an%20elected%20Reeve%2C%20Deputy%20Reeves%2C%20and%20councillors%20the%20number%20of%20which%20depend%20on%20the%20population%20of%20the%20township.%20Its%20responsibilities%20relate%20largely%20to%20the%20upkeep%20of%20the%20local%20road%20system%20and%20the%20delivery%20of%20services%20such%20as%20water%20and%20sewage.%20It%20has%20wide%20powers%20relating%20to%20the%20regulation%20of%20land%20and%20local%20administration%20through%20by-laws.%20It%20has%20the%20power%20to%20raise%20money%20through%20direct%20taxation%20on%20land%20and%20through%20the%20use%20of%20debentures.%20The%20Township%20of%20Ryde%20was%20dissolved%20and%20incorporated%20into%20the%20Town%20of%20Gravenhurst%20in%201971%20under%20the%20District%20Municipality%20of%20Muskoka%20Act%2C%20Ontario%20Statutes%201970%2C%20Chapter%2032.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThis%20act%20provided%20for%20the%20creation%20of%20municipal%20governments%20at%20the%20town%2C%20village%20and%20township%20levels%20and%20identified%20those%20which%20would%20automatically%20be%20granted%20municipal%20status%20when%20the%20act%20came%20into%20effect%2C%20January%201%2C%201850.%20Communities%20not%20named%20in%20the%20original%20act%20could%20petition%20the%20county%20council%20or%20legislative%20assembly%20for%20incorporation%20on%20reaching%20specified%20population%20levels.%20An%20incorporated%20township%2C%20lower%20tier%20municipality%2C%20has%20a%20council%20consisting%20of%20an%20elected%20Reeve%2C%20Deputy%20Reeves%2C%20and%20councillors%20the%20number%20of%20which%20depend%20on%20the%20population%20of%20the%20township.%20Its%20responsibilities%20relate%20largely%20to%20the%20upkeep%20of%20the%20local%20road%20system%20and%20the%20delivery%20of%20services%20such%20as%20water%20and%20sewage.%20It%20has%20wide%20powers%20relating%20to%20the%20regulation%20of%20land%20and%20local%20administration%20through%20by-laws.%20It%20has%20the%20power%20to%20raise%20money%20through%20direct%20taxation%20on%20land%20and%20through%20the%20use%20of%20debentures.%20Originally%20part%20of%20the%20County%20of%20Ontario%2C%20on%20January%201%2C%201974%20%20it%20absorbed%20the%20Village%20of%20Cannington%20to%20form%20part%20of%20the%20Durham%20Region%20under%20Ontario%20Statutes%2C%201973%2C%20Chapter%2078%2C%20the%20Regional%20Municipality%20of%20Durham%20Act.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThis%20act%20provided%20for%20the%20creation%20of%20municipal%20governments%20at%20the%20town%2C%20village%20and%20township%20levels%20and%20identified%20those%20which%20would%20automatically%20be%20granted%20municipal%20status%20when%20the%20act%20came%20into%20effect%2C%20January%201%2C%201850.%20Communities%20not%20named%20in%20the%20original%20act%20could%20petition%20the%20county%20council%20or%20legislative%20assembly%20for%20incorporation%20on%20reaching%20specified%20population%20levels.%20An%20incorporated%20township%2C%20lower%20tier%20municipality%2C%20has%20a%20council%20consisting%20of%20an%20elected%20Reeve%2C%20Deputy%20Reeves%2C%20and%20councillors%20the%20number%20of%20which%20depend%20on%20the%20population%20of%20the%20township.%20Its%20responsibilities%20relate%20largely%20to%20the%20upkeep%20of%20the%20local%20road%20system%20and%20the%20delivery%20of%20services%20such%20as%20water%20and%20sewage.%20It%20has%20wide%20powers%20relating%20to%20the%20regulation%20of%20land%20and%20local%20administration%20through%20by-laws.%20It%20has%20the%20power%20to%20raise%20money%20through%20direct%20taxation%20on%20land%20and%20through%20the%20use%20of%20debentures.%20The%20Township%20was%20dissolved%20in%201974%20and%20amalgamated%20into%20the%20new%20Town%20of%20Haldimand%20in%20the%20Regional%20Municipality%20of%20Haldimand-Norfolk%20under%20Ontario%20Statutes%201973%2C%20Chapter%2096.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThis%20branch%20was%20created%20in%201991%20as%20one%20of%20the%20two%20branches%20of%20the%20newly%20established%20Operations%20Division%20and%20assumed%20the%20functions%20of%20the%20former%20Occupational%20Health%20and%20Safety%20Division.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThomas%20Walmsley%2C%20son%20of%20Samuel%20and%20Eliza%20Walmsley%20of%20Athol%2C%20Ontario%2C%20was%20born%20in%20Ontario%20on%2013%20February%201859.%20He%20was%20a%20schoolteacher%20in%20Athol%20in%201881%20but%20later%20became%20a%20barrister%2C%20establishing%20a%20practice%20in%20Picton%2C%20Ontario%20about%201890.%20He%20married%20Ada%20F.%20Rorke%20on%2026%20August%201896%2C%20and%20they%20had%20a%20son%2C%20Gordon%20Turnbull%20Walmsley%20who%20later%20joined%20his%20father%27s%20law%20practice.%20Thomas%20Walmsley%20died%20about%201929.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

