<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caTroster%20was%20born%20in%20Toronto%20on%2012%20June%201949.%20%20From%201968%20to%201970%20he%20studied%20in%20the%20honours%20B.A.%20program%20at%20York%20University%20majoring%20in%20film.%20In%201970%2C%20while%20at%20York%20%20he%20produced%20his%20first%20independent%20film%20The%20Spell%20That%20Comes%20After.%20Between%201970%20and%201974%20he%20produced%2C%20through%20Christopher%20Chapman%20Ltd.%2C%20several%20film%20shorts%20for%20Mr.%20Rogers%27%20Neighborhood%20broadcast%20over%20PBS%20in%20the%20United%20States.%20Christopher%20Chapman%20had%20a%20mentoring%20influence%20on%20Troster%27s%20filmmaking%20career.%20%20Troster%20went%20on%20to%20serve%20as%20producer%20and%20researcher%20of%20An%20Outside%20View%20in%201973%2C%20produced%20at%20Nielsen%20Ferns%20Ltd.%2C%20a%2030%20minute%20educational%20TV%20talk%20show%20broadcast%20over%20TV%20Ontario.%20In%201975%20he%20produced%20One%20Afternoon%2C%20an%20experimental%20short%20for%20children%27s%20television%20at%20CBC.%20%20In%201976%20he%20produced%20his%20second%20independent%20film%2C%20Bubbie%20%28or%20My%20Grandmother%27s%20Film%29%2C%20a%20portrait%20of%20his%20grandmother%20Sarah%20Salsberg.%20He%20worked%20as%20a%20film%20editor%20at%20CBC%20television%20in%20Toronto%20from%201976%20to%201979.%20%20Troster%20began%20work%20on%20his%20third%20independent%20film%20Spadina%20by%201980%20and%20completed%20it%20in%201984.%20In%201980%20Troster%20formed%20his%20own%20production%20company%20in%20Toronto%2C%20David%20Troster%20Productions.%20Through%20this%20company%20he%20produced%20films%20and%20videos%20for%20corporate%20clients%20including%20medical%20and%20pharmaceutical%20companies%2C%20major%20banks%20and%20government%20agencies.%20Between%20work%20on%20corporate%20productions%2C%20Troster%20wrote%20scripts%20and%20worked%20to%20create%20films%20of%20his%20own%2C%20a%20number%20of%20%20which%20explored%20gay%20relationships%20%28Jamie%20and%20Eric%2C%20Dear%20John%2C%20Seeing%20Someone%2C%20A%20Family%20Likeness%20and%20Binding%20Offers%29.%20Troster%27s%20documentary%20film%20proposals%20included%20treatments%20of%20the%20lives%20of%20%20music%20artist%2C%20Jackie%20Washington%20and%20filmmaker%2C%20Christopher%20Chapman%2C%20%20as%20well%20as%20political%20figures%2C%20Tommy%20Douglas%20and%20J.B.%20Salsberg%2C%20Troster%27s%20uncle.%20However%2C%20Troster%20was%20not%20able%20to%20complete%20any%20of%20these%20works.%20David%20Troster%20died%20on%2018%20November%201995.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

